'Grabner' is an Austrian surname. Notable people with the surname include:

* Hermann Grabner (1886–1969), Austrian composer and music teacher
* Maximilian Grabner (1905–1948), Austrian Gestapo chief in Auschwitz
* Michael Grabner (born 1987), Austrian professional ice hockey player
* Michelle Grabner (born 1962), American painter
* Siegfried "Sigi" Grabner (born 1975), Austrian professional snowboarder
